WEBVTT

00:03.794 --> 00:05.093
<i>Bones,</i>

00:05.129 --> 00:06.495
you sure you don't
want to run over

00:06.530 --> 00:07.696
your testimony
for the morning?

00:07.731 --> 00:09.364
No need. I'm fully prepared.

00:09.400 --> 00:10.565
Just so you know,

00:10.601 --> 00:11.841
I'm hearing talk of suspension,

00:11.869 --> 00:13.435
possible anger
management classes.

00:13.470 --> 00:16.370
Both a waste of my time
and the FBI's resources.

00:16.407 --> 00:17.639
Bones, you know what?

00:17.674 --> 00:18.940
You punched a suspect.

00:18.976 --> 00:19.976
After that misogynist...

00:20.010 --> 00:21.309
Meninist.

00:21.345 --> 00:22.477
Same thing.

00:22.513 --> 00:24.146
He told you to put
a muzzle on me.

00:24.181 --> 00:25.480
He's lucky all I did
was punch him.

00:25.516 --> 00:26.748
All right, just so you know,

00:26.784 --> 00:28.250
that the, uh,
the Bureau is very big

00:28.285 --> 00:30.419
on accountability and remorse.

00:30.454 --> 00:32.119
But I'm not sorry
for my actions.

00:32.156 --> 00:33.622
Uh-uh.
They don't need to know that.

00:33.657 --> 00:35.657
You're making this
a much larger deal

00:35.692 --> 00:37.058
than it needs to be, Booth.

00:37.094 --> 00:38.960
So there's no scenario

00:38.996 --> 00:40.762
where you-you
could take my advice.

00:40.798 --> 00:43.098
Not off the top of my head,
unlikely.

00:43.133 --> 00:44.366
Okay, I got it.

00:44.401 --> 00:48.370
What if I do that thing, huh?

00:48.405 --> 00:49.638
That thing that you like.

00:49.673 --> 00:51.006
That you wrote about, uh,

00:51.041 --> 00:52.874
in your book on page 187.

00:52.910 --> 00:55.010
Bam.

00:55.045 --> 00:59.047
Well, as much
as I typically enjoy...

01:01.018 --> 01:05.120
...the thing on page 187,

01:05.155 --> 01:09.691
I'm not currently in the mood
for that particular thing.

01:09.726 --> 01:11.026
Ah, here's a good one. 92.

01:11.061 --> 01:12.594
The thing
that you talk about on 92.

01:12.629 --> 01:13.662
You love that.

01:13.697 --> 01:15.430
That involves a jump.
92.

01:15.466 --> 01:18.233
I'm not sure, but, um...

01:18.268 --> 01:20.469
I'll wear the rabbit ears.

01:20.504 --> 01:23.738
I might be persuaded
to take your advice

01:23.774 --> 01:26.575
for the thing on page 214.

01:26.610 --> 01:29.778
214. What's 214?

01:29.813 --> 01:31.413
Ah.

01:31.448 --> 01:32.948
Very tribal.

01:32.983 --> 01:35.417
We are in like Flynn.

01:35.452 --> 01:37.652
214. I will prepare the deck.

01:37.688 --> 01:38.920
I'll grab the masks.

01:43.560 --> 01:45.894
Is it possible
that we just watched

01:45.929 --> 01:48.230
seven Star Wars movies
in a row?

01:48.265 --> 01:50.398
Well, the extreme
pain in my lower back

01:50.434 --> 01:52.000
is making me believe
that it is.

01:52.035 --> 01:53.535
I told you you
should have done

01:53.570 --> 01:54.769
those stretches with me.

01:54.805 --> 01:56.738
Eh, I don't know, you know.

01:56.773 --> 01:58.974
The bridges and
the splitsy things,

01:59.009 --> 02:00.509
that just doesn't come
as naturally to me

02:00.544 --> 02:01.610
as it does to you.

02:01.645 --> 02:02.944
Well, fair enough.

02:02.980 --> 02:04.346
You know, my yoga coach
has mentioned

02:04.381 --> 02:05.614
that I have very open hips.

02:05.649 --> 02:06.882
Oh, yeah?
Mm-hmm.

02:06.917 --> 02:09.383
Yoga dude gettin'
a little handsy?

02:09.419 --> 02:11.987
Is that jealousy I sense?

02:12.022 --> 02:13.388
Why would I be jealous?

02:13.423 --> 02:16.324
It's not like you
and I are...

02:16.360 --> 02:19.194
No, I mean,
of course not.

02:19.229 --> 02:20.762
I mean, I would.

02:20.797 --> 02:22.631
You would?
Would you?

02:22.666 --> 02:24.165
Right now?

02:24.201 --> 02:25.367
It feels like a moment.

02:25.402 --> 02:26.434
And we've already let

02:26.470 --> 02:29.604
so many other moments pass by.

02:32.276 --> 02:33.842
Oh! Oh, oh.
Oh!

02:36.647 --> 02:37.979
Oh, wow, are you okay?

02:38.015 --> 02:38.947
Yeah, no, super, super okay.

02:40.584 --> 02:42.517
It's a dead body.
Wow.

02:42.553 --> 02:44.519
Nothing says romantic
like having your first kiss

02:44.555 --> 02:46.254
interrupted by murder.

02:49.726 --> 02:53.028
Or dirty street water.

02:57.834 --> 02:59.267
This is pretty gnarly.

02:59.303 --> 03:01.303
Yeah,
the victim was discovered

03:01.338 --> 03:04.806
by road crews cleaning up
a mudslide near Baltimore.

03:04.841 --> 03:06.541
Was that cause of death?

03:06.577 --> 03:08.710
I don't think so.

03:08.745 --> 03:11.046
The decomp's pretty advanced,
but the mudslide

03:11.081 --> 03:12.380
sure did a hell
of a job on the remains.

03:12.416 --> 03:13.848
Yeah, you're telling me.

03:13.884 --> 03:16.084
Check out all these fractures
on the X-rays.

03:16.119 --> 03:18.853
That slide was
one bumpy toboggan ride.

03:18.889 --> 03:20.288
Uh, the slightly raised ridge

03:20.324 --> 03:22.657
across the central surface
of the pubis,

03:22.693 --> 03:25.160
plus the
anteriorly-positioned mandible

03:25.195 --> 03:26.561
tell me the victim is female.

03:26.597 --> 03:29.798
And the receding zygomatics

03:29.833 --> 03:32.434
and wear on the dentition
suggest that the victim

03:32.469 --> 03:35.971
is of Negroid descent
and in her early 30s.

03:36.006 --> 03:38.940
Presence of hairy maggot blowfly
larvae suggests the victim

03:38.976 --> 03:40.842
was buried
in a shallow grave,

03:40.877 --> 03:43.612
approximately two weeks
before the mudslide.

03:43.647 --> 03:46.881
That tracks with the vitreous
humor in the remaining eyeball.

03:46.917 --> 03:48.283
Hey, honey,
is your shoulder okay?

03:48.318 --> 03:51.019
Hey, what time is
Brennan's hearing?

03:51.054 --> 03:52.520
Wait, hearing?

03:52.556 --> 03:54.055
What hearing?

03:54.091 --> 03:57.158
I think it's going on right now.

03:57.194 --> 03:59.628
Brennan punched a suspect.

03:59.663 --> 04:01.229
That's a big no-no at the FBI.

04:01.264 --> 04:03.064
Go, Dr. B.

04:03.100 --> 04:04.833
I knew there was a reason
she's my hero.

04:04.868 --> 04:07.469
Yeah, well, I think it's got her
into a bit of trouble now.

04:07.504 --> 04:08.837
Oh, come on.

04:08.872 --> 04:10.171
She's so good at her job,

04:10.207 --> 04:11.373
what could they
possibly do to her?

04:11.408 --> 04:12.707
<i>Dr. Brennan,</i>

04:12.743 --> 04:14.442
I'm not sure you understand

04:14.478 --> 04:16.111
the severity
of the situation.

04:16.146 --> 04:18.680
You assaulted a suspect.

04:18.714 --> 04:20.915
The FBI does not
take that lightly.

04:20.951 --> 04:22.050
Nonsense.

04:22.084 --> 04:23.718
Between the years 1993

04:23.754 --> 04:26.488
and 2011, FBI agents either

04:26.523 --> 04:31.026
injured or killed
150 people using firearms.

04:31.061 --> 04:32.627
Your internal investigations

04:32.663 --> 04:34.796
let each of those agents off
without a charge.

04:34.831 --> 04:37.932
You punched an unarmed man.

04:37.968 --> 04:39.434
And he deserved it.

04:39.469 --> 04:41.202
You seem to believe that

04:41.238 --> 04:43.405
that excuses your actions.

04:43.440 --> 04:45.106
That is correct.

04:46.643 --> 04:49.077
I have no more questions
at this moment.

04:49.112 --> 04:51.112
Tomorrow, we speak
to your partner.

04:51.148 --> 04:54.315
If his testimony goes anything
like yours, Dr. Brennan,

04:54.351 --> 04:58.153
you will no longer be allowed
to work with the Bureau.

04:58.188 --> 05:00.822
The panel is adjourned
until tomorrow.

